PREAMBLE

This work exists to strengthen personal sovereignty: the capacity of
individuals, families, and free federations of nodes to own their tools,
their records, and their futures. It is offered openly so that it may
serve human flourishing and Lasting Generational Prosperity (LGP) —
prosperity that compounds across generations because no one can take
the foundation away.

This license keeps that promise enforceable. You may use this work
freely. What you may not do is capture it, enclose it, or strip out
the sovereignty it was built to protect.

---

1. WHAT YOU MAY DO

Subject to the conditions below, permission is granted, free of charge,
to any person obtaining a copy of this work to:

  a. READ and study the work, in whole or in part;
  b. USE and run the work for any purpose, personal or commercial;
  c. MODIFY the work and build upon it;
  d. REDISTRIBUTE the work, in source or built form;
  e. FORK the work and create derivative works.

Forking is not merely tolerated — it is encouraged. A sovereign work
survives by being replicated, adapted, and carried forward by many
hands. If this project ever fails its own principles, forking it is
the intended remedy.

2. ATTRIBUTION

All copies, substantial portions, forks, and derivative works must
retain clear and visible attribution to the original author:

    Kenneth Mangum (KM-1176)

This includes: this copyright line, this license text, and — in any
public-facing derivative — a plain statement that the work is derived
from the Universal Sovereign Node by Kenneth Mangum (KM-1176).
Attribution may not be buried, minimized, or removed.

Do not use the author's name to endorse a derivative without written
permission. State what your work is derived from; do not imply the
original author built or approved it.

3. SOVEREIGNTY PRESERVATION (the heart of this license)

Every copy, fork, and derivative must preserve the sovereign character
of the work. Concretely, a derivative MUST NOT:

  a. remove, disable, or gate the ability of an operator to run the
     work fully on hardware they control, without requiring accounts,
     remote approval, telemetry, or services owned by the distributor;
  b. lock operator data, records, or state into formats or systems the
     operator cannot read, export, and verify with their own tools;
  c. remove or hollow out the human approval gates (propose → approve
     → execute) so that the work acts on an operator's behalf without
     the operator's consent;
  d. relicense the work or a derivative under terms that would permit
     (a), (b), or (c).

3a. THE CONSTITUTIONAL KERNEL (runtime invariants — license-conditioned)

The permissions in Section 1 are conditioned on preserving four runtime
invariants in any copy, fork, or derivative that executes. Together they
are the Constitutional Kernel:

  K1 — HUMAN PRIMACY. Every material action begins with a living human
       decision and ends in human responsibility. The software proposes;
       a person approves; only then may it execute — and where no human
       gate is present, a material action MUST fail closed: refused and
       recorded, never silently permitted. No derivative may remove,
       bypass, delegate to another machine, or automate away the human
       approval gate on material decisions, nor convert a refusal into
       a default permission. The human is the origin point of decision
       and the holder of its meaning; the software remains, always, an
       instrument.
  K2 — DEFAULT-DENY. Capabilities are denied unless explicitly granted.
       A derivative may add grants; it may not invert the default.
  K3 — AUDIT-IMMUTABLE. Actions of consequence append to a hash-chained,
       replayable record the operator holds. A derivative may extend the
       record; it may not make it silently mutable or optional.
  K4 — CONSTITUTIONAL-VALIDATED EXTENSION. New capabilities enter through
       validation against the operator's declared rules — never by
       silent self-extension.

A fork that strips a Kernel invariant at runtime is outside this license,
regardless of what its source tree claims. Section 3's sovereignty
protections and Section 4's anti-capture protections are read together
with this section: the Kernel is HOW those protections stay true while
the software runs.

4. ANTI-CAPTURE AND ANTI-ENCLOSURE

This work may not be used, incorporated, or redistributed as part of
an effort to enclose it — that is, to convert this commons into a
captive asset. In particular, the following are outside the grant of
this license:

  a. offering the work, or a derivative, as a closed hosted service
     while denying users the source and the practical means to leave
     with their data and run it themselves;
  b. asserting patents, trademarks, digital-rights mechanisms, or
     exclusivity agreements against the work or against others'
     lawful use, forking, or distribution of it;
  c. acquisition, embrace-and-extend, or bundling strategies by any
     entity whose purpose or effect is to make the sovereign use of
     this work impractical for individuals and small federations.

An entity that engages in any of the above forfeits every permission
granted by this license, automatically and immediately, for all copies
and derivatives in its possession or control.

5. SHARE-ALIKE OF SOVEREIGNTY

Derivative works must be distributed under this license or under terms
that preserve, with equal or greater strength, the protections in
Sections 2, 3, and 4. You may add terms (warranty, support, pricing
for your own services) so long as they do not weaken those protections.

6. FEDERATION CLAUSE

Nodes running this work or derivatives may federate freely. No party
may charge rent, demand registration, or impose gatekeeping as a
condition of federation protocol compatibility. The right to peer is
part of the work.

7. NO WARRANTY

THE WORK IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE
AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHOR BE LIABLE FOR ANY
CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING FROM THE WORK OR ITS USE.
YOU RUN A SOVEREIGN NODE; YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR WHAT IT DOES.

8. TERMINATION AND REVIVAL

Violation of Sections 2–6 terminates your rights under this license
automatically. Rights are revived if the violation is fully cured
within 30 days of becoming aware of it, unless the violation was a
capture or enclosure attempt under Section 4, in which case
termination is permanent for the violating entity.

9. INTERPRETATION

Where this license is ambiguous, it is to be read in the direction of
greater operator sovereignty, wider lawful replication, and stronger
resistance to capture — never the reverse.

